article.description: JT Yoho scored 22 points and Wright State beat Bowling Green 83-47 on Sunday.
article.headline: Wright State beats cold-shooting Bowling Green 83-47
article.linkText: Wright State beats cold-shooting Bowling Green 83-47
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio -- JT Yoho scored 22 points and Wright State beat Bowling Green 83-47 on Sunday. Yoho was 7 of 12 from the floor with four 3-pointers and five rebounds. Mark Alstork had 19 points, Joe Thomasson scored 13 points with seven reoubnds and six assists, and Grant Benzinger added 11 points. Wright State (5-7) shot 52 percent and was 13 of 28 from beyond the arc. Ismail Ali paced Bowling Green (7-4) with 12 points. Leading scorers Spencer Parker (15.2) and Zack Denny (13.9) combined to go 4 of 12 for 12 points. The Falcons shot 27.5 percent overall and was 2 of 13 on 3-point attempts. The Raiders used an 11-2 run early in the first half -- including 3-pointers by Yoho and Benzinger -- to build a 35-27 lead at the break. Wright State opened the second half on a 15-4 run and Bowling Green was never able to muster a response. The lead reached 30 on a 3-point play by Alstork with 5:14 to go.
